summary:
Fijne dag! 

My name is Mirta and I am a passionate RMSc student of Social Sciences at the University of Amsterdam ðŸ‡³ðŸ‡± looking to use my strong research and academic skills.

I am a huge fan of social sciences, and I believe they are a necessity to private and public sectors. 

My research interest lies in sociology of music and gender (in)equalities within the music industry, both on micro and macro level. I am currently writing my master's thesis on sexualization, objectification and misogyny within turbo-folk lyrics, employing mixed (both quantitative and qualitative) methodology.

Besides academic work, I love fostering cats in need, travelling and singing. I am a semi-professional singer with loads of experience and achieved collaborations with Jacques Houdek, Maja Blagdan, Marko Tolja and many other prominent names in Croatian music industry.

Feel free to message me as I hope I can provide and give new values to you!
